{"questionId":"17553","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>The diagram shows the curve&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>a</mi></mrow><mi>x</mi></mfrac><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>≠</mo><mn>0</mn></math>.</p>\n<p><img style=\"display:block;margin-left:auto;margin-right:auto;\" src=\"__IMG__/4727e9a519d3069d58c5220c1d18fc8d1338d014.png\"></p>\n<p>The equation of the vertical asymptote of the curve is&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>k</mi></math>.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Write down the value of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>k</mi></math>.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mrow><mi>k</mi><mo>=</mo></mrow></mfenced><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>0</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>(A1)</strong></em><em><strong>&nbsp; &nbsp;(C1)</strong></em>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Award <em><strong>(A1)</strong></em> for an answer of \"<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math>\".</p>\n<p><em><strong><span class=\"mjpage\">[1 mark]</span></strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"17553","referenceCode":"19N.1.SL.TZ0.T_14a","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Write down the value of k.","paper":"1","level":"SL","questionNumber":"a","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 5—Calculus","Topic 5—Calculus","SL 5.3—Differentiating polynomials, n E Z","Topic 5—Calculus","SL 5.4—Tangents and normal"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}